On Sunday, February 27, 2022, popular actress, Faithia Williams, had her grand birthday celebration at the Balmoral Hall of Federal Palace Hotel, Victoria Island, Lagos. The birthday soiree was attended by industry veterans including Ebun Oloyede, Taiwo Hassan, Yomi Fash-Lanso, Iya Ereko, and many others. The Nollywood siren turned 51 on February 5, 2022, and she decided to celebrate the milestone with a lined-up activities that kicked off with a costume party and culminated with the high-octane soiree. Fuji music maestro K1 serenaded guests with tunes from his globally acclaimed Fuji sound.   Veteran Nollywood actor Lari Williams dies     Mercy Aigbe’s ex-husband welcomes new baby     Burna Boy survives ‘bad accident’ with expensive…   With an ancient Egyptian-themed stage, the beautiful mother of two left no stone unturned from her beautiful dresses to the gigantic cake, ushers costume, and other side attractions. One of the highlights of the night was when the actress was joined by her kids, Khalid and Aaliya Balogun at the cake stand. Faithia remains one of the most versatile actresses in Nollywood, excelling as an actress and film producer.  With a career spanning over two decades, Fathia has won numerous awards including the AMAA Awards and the AMVCA.